These are my second pair of Rover pants and they've officially become some of my favorites. The fabric is sturdy yet stretchy and the gusseted crotch is something you never knew you wanted in pants 😮‍💨

I find it interesting how cargo pants are cool now, but I got made fun of for wearing them in middle school 👦🏻😢
The world just ain't ready to admit that 12-year-old Frank was a fashion icon 😤✌🏼 
Really though I do think cargo pants have a solid position in menswear. The pockets add some cool depth to an otherwise plain, linear bottom silhouette. Give 'em a shot if you haven't! 👌🏼

𝗥𝗲𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗻 𝘁𝗼 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺
Had to post a flatlay as my first post of 2024 (y'know back in my day, we called these outfit grids 👴🏻). I post more video these days, but these were the original roots of Styles of Man, so they hold a special place in my heart 🥲

💭 I've been reflecting a lot lately about what type of content I want to create going forward, what type of format yields the most engagement, what you guys want to see etc. and I arrived at the conclusion that I should post whatever the f*ck I want to 😁 

📸 Creating content is not easy. Chasing trends and likes and comments and whichever other vanity metric is nonsensical. It leads only to burnout and a loss of passion. I had to remember what got me into the game in the first place. It's time to become a student once more and accept that some things aren't what they used to be. 

🎥 New YouTube video (first in 2 years oof) of my updated home office coming by the end of the month with more to follow. Honing my skillset behind the scenes to produce content that I'm proud of once again. 

🙏🏼 To those who read my caffeine-fueled ramble to the end and those who've come along in the journey the last few years, I thank you wholeheartedly for the support. More to come. Cheers 🥂
